Keluhan Pax Transit
 Chorology Handling.
 On 05 February 2026, a transit passenger from flight KL835 continued their journey on GA714 to Sydney. During transit monitoring, a staff member captured a photograph of the passenger strictly for internal operational coordination purposes. The intent was to:
 - Confirm that the transit handling process had been completed;
 - Provide situational awareness to the operational team that the passenger was within the correct transit flow;
 - Mitigate the risk of a missing passenger during boarding.

